@Jordan
I started to respond with Cong You Bing, 葱油饼 earlier but then figured you were responding to something in a different puzzle? As far as I know, yakitori,  焼き鳥, which literally means "grilled bird," refers to chicken, often on skewers.

I don't particularly want to work the Midi to see if there was something about grilled bird there because then Games would tell me I had a 2-day streak and guilt me for not working it tomorrow.

